Continuing on from this (sorry for the comment spam), I think it would make sense to 

1. rename the current function to `tbl_isarray` (because it corresponds fully to the definition of "array" in the Lua documentation);
2. add a _new_ `tbl_islist` that implements your changed check;
3. give an explicit definition of "array" and "list" in each docstring to make the difference obvious.

(Reminder to me: This is technically a breaking change either way, so don't forget to add this to the Following HEAD issue.)
